<seg id="1">Warren plans to take a 'hard look' at running for president</seg>
<seg id="2">U.S. Sen. Elizabeth Warren says she'll take a "hard look at running for president" after the November elections.</seg>
<seg id="3">The Boston Globe reports the Massachusetts Democrat spoke about her future during a town hall in western Massachusetts Saturday.</seg>
<seg id="4">Warren, a frequent critic of President Donald Trump, is running for re-election in November against GOP state Rep. Geoff Diehl, who was co-chairman of Trump's 2016 Massachusetts campaign.</seg>
<seg id="5">She has been at the center of speculation that she might take on Trump in 2020.</seg>
<seg id="6">Saturday afternoon's event in Holyoke was her 36th meeting with constituents using the town hall format since Trump took office.</seg>
<seg id="7">An attendee asked her if she planned to run for president.</seg>
<seg id="8">Warren replied that it's time "for women to go to Washington to fix our broken government, and that includes a woman at the top."</seg>
</p>
